            . I lodge at Draper's, in Kent-street. On Whit Monday I met the prisoner, he asked me if I wanted to buy a coat or jacket? I said No. He shewed me the clock, I said I had only 5 s. - he tied it up and went on; he then called me and said as I was a poor man I should have it.</p>
